// AdMob configuration — template.
//
// COPY this file to `Tuist/AdMob.xcconfig` (gitignored) and fill in the
// real values for whichever app you're building. The real file must NEVER
// be committed.
//
// On a fresh clone:
//   cp Tuist/AdMob.xcconfig.example Tuist/AdMob.xcconfig
//   # then edit Tuist/AdMob.xcconfig and replace the values below with
//   # the production IDs for the app you're building (or leave the test
//   # values for sandbox/debug verification).
//   mise exec -- tuist generate
//
// Real production IDs are NOT documented here — they live in the project's
// private memory (`admob-production-ids` for Sudoku, `minesweeper-admob-ids`
// for Minesweeper). Ask the project owner if you need them.
//
// For CI (Xcode Cloud): no manual setup needed. The following env vars
// must be defined in ASC → Xcode Cloud → Workflow → Environment Variables
// (marked Secret), one set per workflow / app:
//
//   SUDOKU_ADMOB_APP_ID
//   SUDOKU_ADMOB_BANNER_UNIT_ID
//   MINESWEEPER_ADMOB_APP_ID
//   MINESWEEPER_ADMOB_BANNER_UNIT_ID
//
// `ci_scripts/ci_post_clone.sh` reads them and writes `Tuist/AdMob.xcconfig`
// before `tuist generate` runs, selecting the right values per workflow.
//
// The values below are Google's UNIVERSAL TEST IDs (publicly documented —
// safe for sandbox / debug verification). They will NOT serve real
// production creatives. See:
// https://developers.google.com/admob/ios/test-ads#sample_ad_units

ADMOB_APP_ID = ca-app-pub-3940256099942544~1458002511
ADMOB_BANNER_UNIT_ID = ca-app-pub-3940256099942544/2934735716
